anysection.section module

class anysection.section.Section(name)[source]

Bases: object

Class representing a structural section composed of fibers.

add_area(area_obj, dx=0, dy=0)[source]

Add an area object (CompositeArea, Rectangle, Circle, etc.) to the section.

Parameters:

  • area_obj (Area) – An area object that has an area() and centroid() method.

  • dx (float) – Shift in x-direction.

  • dy (float) – Shift in y-direction.

add_fiber(area, x, y, material)[source]

Add a fiber to the section.

Parameters:

  • area (float) – Area of the fiber.

  • x (float) – X-coordinate of the fiber centroid.

  • y (float) – Y-coordinate of the fiber centroid.

  • material (Material) – Material object (Concrete, Steel, etc.)

centroid()[source]

Calculate the centroid of the section.

moment_of_inertia()[source]

Calculate the moment of inertia of the section.

total_area()[source]

Calculate the total area of the section.

class anysection.solver.SectionSolver(section)[source]

Bases: object

Class to perform section analysis to determine axial forces, moments, and moment-curvature relationships using iterative solvers.

calculate_axial_force(neutral_axis, curvature)[source]

Calculate the axial force in the section for a given neutral axis position and curvature.

Parameters:

  • neutral_axis (float) – Position of the neutral axis.

  • curvature (float) – Curvature applied to the section.

Returns:

Total axial force.

Return type:

float

calculate_moment_capacity(curvature, neutral_axis)[source]

Calculate bending moment for a given curvature and neutral axis.

Parameters:

  • curvature (float) – Section curvature.

  • neutral_axis (float) – Position of the neutral axis.

Returns:

Resulting moment.

Return type:

float

find_neutral_axis(target_axial_force, curvature, tolerance=1e-06, max_iter=100)[source]

Find the neutral axis depth that satisfies the target axial force.

Parameters:

  • target_axial_force (float) – Applied axial force.

  • curvature (float) – Section curvature.

  • tolerance (float) – Convergence tolerance.

  • max_iter (int) – Max iterations.

Returns:

Neutral axis position.

Return type:

float

interaction_curve(neutral_axis_range)[source]

Generate the interaction curve (axial force vs. bending moment).

Parameters:

neutral_axis_range (tuple) – (min, max) range for the neutral axis.

Returns:

List of (axial_force, bending_moment) tuples.

Return type:

list

moment_curvature_analysis(curvature_range, axial_force=0.0)[source]

Perform moment-curvature analysis for a specified axial force.

Parameters:

  • curvature_range (iterable) – List or array of curvature values.

  • axial_force (float) – Applied axial force (positive = compression).

Returns:

List of (curvature, moment) tuples.

Return type:

list
